# 🔐 Encrypted Password Manager

A secure command-line password manager built in **Python** that stores credentials in an encrypted local vault using **Argon2id** and **AES-256-GCM**.

This project was created to demonstrate secure software development, modern cryptography, and object-oriented programming.

---

## Features

- Encrypts credentials using AES-256-GCM
- Protects the master password with Argon2id
- Add, retrieve, update, list, and delete credentials
- Generate cryptographically secure passwords
- Secure local JSON vault
- Atomic file writes to reduce corruption
- Command-line interface built with `argparse`

---

## Technologies

- Python
- Argon2id
- Cryptography
- AES-256-GCM
- JSON
- argparse
- pathlib
- dataclasses

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/davian3x/password-manager.git
cd password-manager
pip install -e .
```

---

## Usage

Create a vault

```bash
password-manager init
```

Add credentials

```bash
password-manager add github.com myusername --notes "Personal Account"
```

Retrieve credentials

```bash
password-manager get github.com
```

List saved credentials

```bash
password-manager list
```

Delete credentials

```bash
password-manager delete github.com
```

Generate a secure password

```bash
password-manager generate --length 24 --symbols
```

---

## Security

- AES-256-GCM authenticated encryption
- Argon2id key derivation
- Random cryptographic salts
- Random AES-GCM nonces
- Master password is never stored
- Passwords are never written to disk in plaintext

